  "prompt": "Does Reliance JIO 4G require internet to make voice calls?",
  "response": "Reliance Jio uses Voice over LTE (VoLTE) technology for making voice calls, which technically does not require a separate internet connection, as it uses the LTE data network to transmit calls. This means that as long as you have a 4G LTE signal from Jio, you can make and receive voice calls.\n\nHowever, VoLTE is different from traditional voice calls that use circuit-switched networks (like 2G or 3G). Instead, it uses the data network to route voice calls. So, it doesn't require an active internet data plan, but it does require a 4G connection to utilize this functionality.",
